      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted per Celik et al. 2008 GCI methodology. Mesh sizes: coarse 1.2M, medium 3.8M, fine 9.1M cells. GCI_fine = 1.18% for hemolysis scalar at worst-case operating point. Observed convergence order p=1.94. Fine mesh selected for all production runs. Discretization error bounded and documented in VR-002."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-mrl2-criteria",
      "rationale": "FDA experimental hemolysis data collected under controlled laboratory conditions replicating CPB operating parameters: flow rates 2.5–5.0 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM, bovine blood hematocrit 33±2%. Temperature maintained at 37°C ±0.5°C. Test conditions documented in FDA benchmark protocol and confirmed consistent with COU operating envelope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-mrl2-criteria",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against FDA experimental measurements at 5 operating conditions. Mean normalized RMSE = 0.087. All predicted values within 95% prediction interval of experimental data. RH < 1 at all operating points confirming model correctly identifies hemolysis-safe operating envelope relative to predicate device."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl2-criteria",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH) computed from CFD-derived shear stress history along Lagrangian particle tracks. These QoIs are directly mapped to the clinical endpoint of pump-induced hemolysis and are the quantities measured in the FDA experimental benchmark. QoI relevance confirmed by clinical literature and FDA guidance on hemolysis testing."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl2-criteria",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry — the same device class and flow regime as the COU. Operating conditions in validation (2.5–5.0 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM) span the COU operating envelope. Blood analog properties matched to COU conditions. Validation scenario assessed as directly relevant to COU without extrapolation beyond validated domain."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-scopeout-mrl2",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, separate quantification of numerical solver error beyond code verification is not required. Solver accuracy is addressed through the Numerical code verification factor (VR-003) which demonstrates convergence order consistent with theoretical expectations. Scoping out this factor is consistent with ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 1 requirements at MRL 2 for this device class and decision consequence level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-scopeout-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment is not required at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 1. The simulation workflow is executed by trained CFD engineers with documented competency records. Standard operating procedures (SOP-CFD-001) govern simulation setup, execution, and post-processing. Peer review of simulation inputs and outputs conducted prior to submission. Scoped out consistent with MRL 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-scopeout-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Formal model form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2. The SST k-omega turbulence model with power-law hemolysis damage accumulation (Giersiepen et al. formulation) is the established approach for CFD hemolysis prediction in centrifugal blood pumps per FDA guidance and peer-reviewed literature. Model form adequacy is implicitly addressed through the output comparison factor demonstrating acceptable agreement with experimental data."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-scopeout-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Comprehensive model input uncertainty propagation is not required at MRL 2. Key input sensitivities (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, blood viscosity) are addressed through the Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification documented in the hemolysis benchmark validation result. Remaining inputs (geometry, boundary conditions) are tightly constrained by the FDA benchmark protocol. Scoped out consistent with MRL 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-scopeout-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Statistical characterization of test sample variability beyond what is captured in the FDA experimental dataset is not required at MRL 2. The FDA benchmark dataset includes replicate measurements at each operating condition enabling assessment of experimental repeatability. Sample-to-sample variability in bovine blood properties is within the documented hematocrit tolerance of ±2%. Scoped out consistent with MRL 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/equivalency-scopeout-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Formal equivalency assessment of input parameters between validation scenario and COU is not required at MRL 2. The validation and COU share the same device geometry, operating range, and blood analog properties. Differences in hematocrit between bovine blood (validation) and human blood (COU) are within the range documented in published hemolysis model sensitivity studies showing less than 4% variation in NIH predictions. Scoped out consistent with MRL 2 requirements."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The CFD hemolysis model for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump is accepted for the stated COU at MRL 2. All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels: Software QA achieved Gradation 3 (required 2); Numerical code verification, Discretization error, Test conditions, Output comparison, QoI relevance, and Validation relevance each achieved Gradation 2 (required 2). Six factors (Numerical solver error, Use error, Model form, Model inputs, Test samples, Equivalency of input parameters) are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 with documented rationale. The model demonstrates RH < 1 at all 5 operating conditions with mean NRMSE = 0.087 against FDA experimental benchmark data. Monte Carlo uncertainty analysis confirms RH < 1 at 97.3% of sampled parameter combinations. Mesh convergence GCI_fine = 1.18% is well within acceptable limits. The validation scenario is directly relevant to the COU with no extrapolation beyond the validated operating domain. The structured evidence base, complete provenance chain from experimental data through validation activities to simulation outputs, and satisfactory performance across all assessed factors support acceptance of the model for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for this Class II CPB device.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
